The defendant Kevin Jay Koethe was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of amended Ct 1 Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order w/o repeater in 16CM52. Crt accepts plea and finds DE guilty of OWI 1st in 16TR1140. Sentencing arguments. 20 days to file appeal.

-   S/W 1 year probation. Report to probation no later than 2:00 p.m. on 06-21-2016. Bond will continue until reports to probation.

- AODA and compliance of treatment plan

- Complete all other programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the Department of Corrections

- It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Jennifer K. - DNA Sample and Surcharge of $200.00
